docs.lead_paragraph: The Justice Department has reached a $134,000 settlement with a New York woman after federal drug agents used information from her cellphone to set up a fake Facebook page in her identity, a tactic that raised privacy concerns and led to a federal government review of the ruse, according to court papers filed Tuesday.

docs.lead_paragraph: The most overused word in sports is "star." It should be reserved only for the deserving few, those who constantly brighten our horizons with their exploits, who don't wax, wane and flame out in a season or two and, most importantly, who don't cheat, dope, act like idiots and otherwise prove that sports are too quick to build pedestals for athletes.
